Don't like my review? Here's a recipe for Fish and Chips:

Ingredients

For the fries:

1 gallon safflower oil
4 large Russet potatoes
Kosher salt

For the batter:

2 cups flour
1 tablespoon baking powder
1 teaspoon kosher salt
1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper
Dash Old Bay Seasoning
1 bottle brown beer, cold
1 1/2 pounds firm-fleshed whitefish (tilapia, pollock, cod), cut into 1-ounce strips
Cornstarch, for dredging

Let's Start!

Heat oven to 200 degrees F.

Heat the safflower oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat until it reaches 320 degrees.

Using a V-slicer with a wide blade, slice the potatoes with the skin on. Place in a large bowl with cold water.

In a bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, salt, cayenne pepper, and Old Bay seasoning. Whisk in the beer until the batter is completely smooth and free of any lumps. Refrigerate for 15 minutes. Note: The batter can be made up to 1 hour ahead of time.

Drain potatoes thoroughly, removing any excess water. When oil reaches 320 degrees, submerge the potatoes in the oil. Working in small batches, fry for 2 to 3 minutes until they are pale and floppy. Remove from oil, drain, and cool to room temperature.

Increase the temperature of the oil to 375 degrees. Re-immerse fries and cook until crisp and golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove and drain on roasting rack. Season with kosher salt while hot and hold in the oven.

Allow oil to return to 350 degrees. Lightly dredge fish strips in cornstarch. Working in small batches, dip the fish into batter and immerse into hot oil. When the batter is set, turn the pieces of fish over and cook until golden brown, about 2 minutes. Drain the fish on the roasting rack. Serve with malt vinegar.

Never played this game but steam say that I actually did so instead of judging the game here's a cool way to make skinny guacamoles with homemade baked tortilla chips :

Skinny Guacamole:

2 medium green sweet peppers
2 medium fresh poblano chile peppers
1 bulb garlic
1/2 teaspoon olive oil
2 roma tomatoes, seeded and chopped
1 serrano pepper, minced
2 medium ripe avocados, halved, seeded, peeled, and diced
1 teaspoon lime zest
2 tablespoons lime juice
1/2 teaspoon salt

Baked Tortilla Chips:

Corn tortillas
Olive oil spray
Salt

For the guacamole:

Preheat oven to 425° F. Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with foil; set aside. Quarter, stem, and seed the peppers. Place pepper quarters, cut sides down, in the prepared pan. Cut off the top half inch of the garlic bulb to expose ends of individual cloves. Leaving garlic bulb whole, remove any loose, papery outer layers. Place bulb, cut end up, on a double thickness of foil. Drizzle with the oil. Bring foil up around bulb and fold edges together to loosely enclose. Place foil packet on the pan with the peppers.
Roast peppers and garlic for 20 to 30 minutes or until pepper skins are charred and garlic cloves feel soft. Allow to cool about 15 minutes. When garlic head is cool enough to handle, squeeze garlic paste out of the individual cloves.
In a food processor combine roasted pepper quarters and the garlic paste. Cover and pulse until combined, but still slightly chunky.
In a large bowl, combine tomatoes and serrano pepper. Add roasted pepper and garlic combination and stir to combine. Add diced avocado, lime zest, lime juice, and salt. Gently toss to combine.
Serve immediately or cover the surface with plastic wrap and chill for up to 1 hour.
For the chips:

Cut corn tortillas into wedges and place on a foil-lined baking sheet. Spray lightly with olive oil spray and season with salt, to taste.
Bake in a 350° F oven for 8-10 minutes or until lightly golden brown.

reviewText: Early Access Review\n\nGreat game! And if you were wondering, this is NOT a pay 2 win game! There is a shop in the main menu, but the only things you can buy are badges and skins which are only cosmetic features for your soldier. They do not help you gain an unfair advantage unlike most free 2 play FPS games. Every gun you cam get is earned through getting kills, which award you with in-game cash to buy better guns. My tip to get more kills in this game is to: 1. By a SPAS-12 shotgun at the very start of the match -> 2. Kill enough dudes until you can afford the AK-47 -> 3. After you buy the AK, kill more dudes until you can afford the maximum 100 point body armor. 4. Now that you have the basic needs, you can continue killing until you can afford an AWP or LMG -> 5. Repeat same steps in next match. This tactic works best for me and it's helped me improve my game a lot (With this strategy, I get over a 2 KD average each match). Another piece of advice is to just hip fire, don't bother aiming down the sights unless you are holding down a choke point or using a sniper rifle. Spraying and praying will kill people ALOT better/faster than ADSing. Trust me. Oh. Also, if you meet some good/skilled players along the way, ask them to friend request you. If you have a massive team of good players, you will just rekt the ♥♥♥♥ out of ALL the noobs that try to fight back. Overall, this game is really worth a try. Like most reviews I've seen, this game is like a CS and CoD hybrid. So, is you're a fan of either these games, chances are, this game will be a ton of fun for you. But, if you don't like it, just delete it and no harm is done. Besides, the game is only like 200 MB, so it doesn't take up much space anyway. That's about it for what I have to say. Have fun!

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Welll, I don't know what to say about this one, yet. I do enjoy it, it's basically CS meets CoD, which is kind of a...Bad thing, I guess?

You can buy stuff with the money you get after killing people, pretty much like in CS. You can get better weapons, armor, grenades, lots of stuff like that. Also, lots of weapons from counter strike games appear here, which is a plus.

On the other hand, it resembles CoD, mostly because there is almost zero recoil when you aim down the sights and enemies are bullet sponges. BUT, this game doesn't allow you to go prone, so that's a big ♥♥♥♥ing plus over CoD.

Music is meh, controls are standard when it comes to FPS games, so there is not much to complain about that.Guns are re-skins at the moment, which kind sucks. Just pick the one with the most ammo and the best iron sights.

So far, this game is midly entertaining, albeit kinda generic, gameplay wise. You can buy all the weapons in the game without having to use real cash, which is amazing, so it's definitely not P2W. For an early access F2P game, it's not as bad as I expected, I expected something ♥♥♥♥♥♥ like Tactical Intervention.

Also, I dunno if it's just me, or the game itself, but there's LOTS of lag spikes all the time, even in US servers. I dunno what's this all about. Also, it's extremely easy to spawncamp, spawns are mostly small spaces with two entrances, just put players on each exit and farm kills. That definitely needs to get fixed. I've seen games where one of the teams can't even get out of the spawn, at all. It's fun when you are on the camping team, but if not...It's pretty damn frustrating.

Also, what pretty can kill this game...Sometimes, even if you play on servers close to you, the game's got a serious problem with lag. And with sometimes, I'm talking about 8/10 servers you try to access. When you find a good, not so laggy server, you're all set.

So far, this game is a mixed bag. I do like it, but it gets stale after a while, plus, if you are expecting something extremely good, you will be dissapointed. Just give it a try, see for yourself, it's free to play after all.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_xKEtMzXetI

Some footage I got from my 3rd or so time playing for anyone curious on how it looks.

This is one of those games that has an alright idea (take weapons and characters similar to Counter Strike and merge it with Call of Duty-esque gameplay) but it struggles a lot due to the bugs and the quality of the game over all. I have a lot of issues with connecting to servers and most of the time I get audio errors which cause all my sound in game to be delayed.

The core mechanics of the game could use a lot of work as well. The price of some of the guns are very steep compared to how much you earn per kill, enough so that if you want one of the better sniper rifles you will be running around most of the game with a pistol trying to kill people with AK's and shotguns just to try and afford it. However some of the most powerful weapons are priced extremely cheap. The Spas hits like and absolute truck (argubly overpowered, you can snipe with it) and you can buy it as soon as you get in the game. The price of some of the guns also causes you to be stuck with whatever gun you buy the entire game.

The movement feels very floaty and you never really feel like your character is touching the floor as well as the aiming just feels off at times. Characters often bug out and will run through walls or completely disappear. What I have ran into a lot has been seeing enemies who appear to just be running, they are not aiming at me at all and don't appear to be looking at me, just to have my character randomly die from them.

There are a ton of bugs in this game at the moment and it really feels borderline unplayable. However with that being said the game is in early access and it's clear to see what the developers are trying to do with the game. There are a lot of small things in this game that I think they're doing well. It's a simple design, the game doesnt feel cluttered and over complicated. The idea of a kind of CS meets CoD type FPS is intriguing and one that I think could be executed well with the right team behind it. I'm going to recommend this game even with it's faults under the assumption that the developers really put the time in to cleaning the game up and improving on it, It's very rough around the edges right now but the potential for a really fun game is here.

reviewText: Early Access Review\n\nThere are two kinds of bad games that exist in the wild: Those that know that they are bad, and those that are bad and try fruitlessly to be good. Guess which one Warmode is? First off: Warmode is about as generic of a shooter as you can get, it features the bland, old formula of Terrorists VS. Counter-Terrorists that we’ve seen a million times now. It features a generic cast of weapons from M4’s to P90’s snipers, shotguns, etc. etc. You’d be forgiven in thinking that this game doesn’t sound all THAT bad, I mean come on, it’s just sounds like some generic shooter dreamt up by some Call of Duty fanboy who payed a moderate amount attention in his 11th grade computer science class to learn the basics of coding enough to get a copy of Insert Generic Game Engine Here to make a first person shooter, but the real meat of this game is in its mechanics, or lack of. This game has about THE most broken mechanics I have ever seen in a shooter, and I’m not talking about “Promised game-changing mechanics are clucky and gimmicky”, no. I’m talking about the fundamental parts of what makes modern FPS games tick are broken and glitch. All guns for some strange reason the same accuracy spread, you can iron sight while reloading, this doesn’t even matter, because iron sighting doesn’t help much regardless, the KNIFE has accuracy, so you basically have to be standing still in order to knife someone, sometimes you randomly die without any mention of who killed you, or how you died, and that’s just scratching the surface of how broken this game is. The maps are too small to have any meaningful firefight, with the exception of one map, two of the maps are still in block out with placeholder textures spewed everywhere, the spawn protection gives no indication of when it where’s off, leading you to empty full magazines into the opponent, only for him to notice your presence and promptly take you out like he’s God or something, and on occasion, you are flung into the air like you’ve been scooped up by a magical, invisible, tornado, only to return to the ground unharmed (Because of course this game doesn’t have fall damage). Overall, you’re better off making your own shooter than to play this peace of crap excuse for a multiplayer game.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

This is a bad f2p russian counter-strike knockoff, without anything that makes CS good.

All the guns feel samey and many of them are nigh useless (shotguns and snipers specifically), with one of the cheapest (the AK-47) being easily the best gun in the game, with the machine guns (PKM and M249) being nice runnerups, only not the best because you can only get them late in the match when you've had a good kill count.

The maps are poorly designed, with the best designed map being a straight rip of A side/mid from dust2. Some of them are literally aim maps (which exist in cs only to keep you from being distracted, not because the textureless aesthetic is good).

As far as I can tell, all the servers are in russia, so if you're in the states or probably even europe, prepare for lag. A lot of it. In particularly bad servers, you can even kill yourself by walking into your own knife stabs. Yep.

There is only one game mode: TDM, instant respawn, first team to 150 kills.

Other reviews talk about cheaters, but I haven't seen any myself after about 3 hours of games. I went to see if there were any hacks available, but they were all outdated and/or patched. There may be more on a russian site I simply can't access, since it's probably more popular there, but on english sites there seems to be no interest in cheating on this game. It's not like you need to cheat, anyway- everyone is trash, and if you use even a semi decent weapon, you can easily top the scoreboard. Seriously, no one is good at this game. If they're complaining about a hacker, it's probably just someone that's more than a silver 2 on cs.

Instead of an anti-cheat, there's a kick system which bans the person from the server for a few hours if it succeeds. That's terrible. I had several attempts to kick me today (which didn't succeed) for simply doing well or getting a good kill spree. Still, another hallmark of a terrible shooter.

The guns feel awful, everything is flaccid, bugs are rampant, TDM is boring, etc etc. There's a lot wrong with this game. it surprises me anyone even thinks there's something good about it. You can get CS for like, $6 on sale. Is that really too much?

reviewText:
Early Access Review

*WARNING* I came across bugs that caused the textures on screen to flash rapidly. Hurt my eyes. Plus if you're prone to epileptic seizures be aware. Happened after I changed my graphics settings. It could have been my graphics card overheating, but I highly doubt it. See my screenshots if you're curious. For that reason I would recommend restarting your game after changing graphics, as it appears to fix the problem.

If you've ever played F2P shooters like Project: Blackout and the like, this is basically a simple version of that. Buy guns with accrued cash as the game progresses. Don't lose your guns when you die, like you do in CS. 1 game mode, 4 maps.

I like this game because it offers the quick bang for your buck I want in shooters, and runs very well on lower end computers.

You may be used to early access games being optimized poorly, but I am able to get a solid 60+ FPS almost constantly at low and 1440x900 rez. Even with the textures set to low, the game still looks good. No need to complain.

Yes, some of the game is in russian, but only non essential parts. I'm sure this will be fixed with time. Currently there are no paid features enabled, which I like.

If you enjoy shooting virtual enemies just cause, I would recommend this game. (^_^)b

This game is heavily inspired by Counter Strike, one of the maps was a clone of de_dust2, it also has some COD mechanics aswell. Overall, I enjoyed the game.

**Updated
Warmode is basically the minimum viable product of both Counter Strike, and Call of Duty. It shares map design, and crosshair style with CS, but has coating of Call of Duty gun play mechanics. There are a ton of guns to choose from, but after playing the game for a couple matches, you can soon see which are the best.

However, despite flaws in a huge amount of bugs, this game is enjoyable. I enjoyed playing this with my friends, I enjoyed playing it alone, basically you just shoot enemies, and it does a great job at getting straight to the point. This is why I would recommened this game to anyone who just wants to start a game, and start shooting.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

WARMODE is a Counter-Strike style FPS. 2 teams face off against each other, slaughering each other until the score limit is reached.

The Good FREE: A free FPS on Steam which ISN'T p2w: only things you CAN buy are cosmetics (masks, badges)
Variety of weapons: Pistols, shotguns, rifles, snipers, LMG's and more
Counter-Strike inspired
No one actually cares about your character level or rank
The community is better than most online games: No kicking because you are noob
Mildly realistic: You have to stand still to aim properly
You don't lose your weapons when you die: When you buy it, it's yours to keep for the rest of the match.
It's fun, y'know, that strange feeling no one has anymore
Everyone is too focused on getting headshots to abuse you in chat
Running up and knifing people is both hillarious and effectiveThe BadSpawn camping is rather easy and is abused
Lag is real for non-Russains/people outside the US/EU
The occasional non-friendly person
The amount of Russain:US servers is too damm highThe NeutralDeagle/M4A1 general strat is boring
Only one gamemode: But seriously, with a game called WARZONE, I don't expect much apart from Team Deathmatch style.
Strange physics: Recoil is strange when zoomed in and bullets drop have a drop, which really doesn't matter
TL:DR: WARZONE is Counter-Strike but less challenging, more fun, completely free, and worth the time you invest. If the devs get more servers up in more places and don't turn this into a p2w, then this will continue to be a great game.

8/10

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Welcome. Let us get started, gentlemen.

Here is an example of a casual online shooter. Yes, I have just said casual. If what you seek is competitive gameplay I just can not recommend this game to you.

Some thoughts on visual and technical sides:The biggest advantage of this game is that its system requirements are unbeliveably low.
The graphics are matching the requirements though, so do not expect miracles.
Still, models of characters and weapons look polished.
The game on my Q8200 paired with 9800GT 1 GB is very smooth, but sometimes very annoying laggs appear on the map Pripyat (I do not know whether they are an optimisation flaw or server capacity issue.)
Gameplay experience:The only existing gamemode is team deathmatch called skirmish.
Gameplay is very dynamic thanks to small maps and 8 vs 8 player cap.
On the other side it often ultimately leads to spawnraping chaos, people running around with knives etc.
Let me visualize how small the maps are - a sniper camping at the end of your path can be mostly reached with a grenade or quickly killed with any AR.
There are many different weapons divided into classes such as Pistols, ARs, SMGs, Heavy etc. (You will not find any informations about their damage or rate of fire though.)
However, you mostly stick with just few of them as their poor iron sights (i.e. FAMAS), blinding muzzle flash covering half of the screen that simply makes continuous fire and aiming unreliable or overall poor performance (Pistol and SMG issue mostly.)
The damage system is somewhat strange, headshots instantly lead to death no matter which weapon you are using and how much armor you have. You often need a couple of chest shots to kill an opponent and enemy legs are made of titanium, so forget about getting someone from 100% to 0% by shooting at his legs. People that score headshots benefit, that is good, but at the same time this often leads to ridiculous situations where glock randomly beats an AK-47.
There is an item-shop, but only cheap visual effects can be bought there.

The biggest flaw of this game so far? Hackers, yes - and I am not talking about good people as you will meet many of decent players easily reaching K/D over 4. I am talking about people using unlimited ammo or increased rate of fire.
Conclusion?If I could I would give this game rather neutral recommendation due to some frustrating inconveniences, but its somewhat addicting character and presence of one more game" syndrome turn it into an excellent time filler."

reviewText:
Early Access Review

This FPS is a mix between Counter-Strike mechanics and Call of Duty fast gameplay, wich makes this game pretty fun.
The game suffers of a lack of quality as it looks, but the final product can give you some hours of fun with friends and skirmishing alone.

It has microtransactions as it is a F2P, but the most noticeable difference wich makes this game pretty balanced is all the available weapons are usable for everyone when you first enter the game, giving you the opportunity to get them with In-Match currency that you earn by receiving frags and assists. That's right, weapons are earned by In-Match money, similar to Counter-Strike. The only thing purchable on the store are badges and masks for your character.

Gameplay is fast paced, aim mechanic is a mix between the Dynamic Croshair from CS and Aim-Down-Sights from CoD, wich makes this game pretty unique and fitting to all kind of FPS players. But, lacks of in-game tutorial, wich is simply a screen with all the button layout, wich for efortless players wanting to play the game right away is a bit overwhelming.

In conclusion, the game needs a bit more love by the developers and players, it's not a bad game, it's not horrible, it's not the best FPS but it's fun, playable and can run on Low-Class PC's. What more do you want? Give it a try and download it. You won't regret it!

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Quad Feed: The video game!

What to say about Warmode? Well, as an early access FPS and a name like Warmode I was expecting to play a Warface rip-off but was pleasently surprised when I jumped into a game when it wasn't. Yes it looks and feels like the disabled child of counter-strike and CoD 4 but as it is Warmode is pretty solid. I always like playing these new FPS's especialy early access as it's always nice to see a game develop and improve with age. Killing enemies in Warmode sure is fun as you can repeatedly shoot a guy in the groin for a good 3 seconds with an AK47 and he can finish you off with a swift kill to the head with his pistol but then again it feels good to kill a guy with your pistol whilst he shoots you in the groin for a good 3 seconds with an AK47. Playing Warmode took me back to my halo 3 SWAT days where headshots really do matter. No p2w aspects, if you want you can pay 99 cents for a little tiger mask if that's your thing.

Pros:
- Weapons are solid and balanced
- Instant respawn
- Guns Look cool
- Great time killer
- System friendly

Cons:
- A few bugs (Tells me I have a grenade when I don't, sometimes killstreaks carry on after death)
- Maps are teeny weeny and very few
- no collateral. once your bullet hits an enemy it's gone. Forever.
- Hit makers on friendlys
- Some text is in broken english

reviewText:
Early Access Review

First off, this is early access so things are prone to change as the game develops.
This game man, even though I have only a few hours on it, I can easly say this is one of my favorite games to play. The game although brand new is amazing, It's sorta a mixture of call of duty and counterstrike, but with a few less features, although this game is good there are some bad things to it that im hoping get fixed when the debugining begins.

BUGS AND THINGS I DONT LIKE ABOUT THE GAME

-Some guns are just way to powerful to be fair (Friggen heavy weapons and sguns).
- Aim down sights are basically useless, all guns are rediculously accurate standing still and while crouching, all you have to   do is aim below the head because after you shoot 2 bullets when aiming down sight, all the other bullets are landing above the crosshair.
-Knifing: although its very strong (people running arround knifing the crap out of people). It is sorta buggy, if you knife someone it doesnt allways register.
- teamates allways soaking up the freaking bullets ( Stand infront of you while you are killing someone ). The bullets end up in the teamate litterally standing infront of you and not in the enemy, it gets annoying.
-The BattleField4 Hit reg. Bullets dont register as a hit when you want them to.
-Some maps are way unfiar, when it comes to base ♥♥♥♥. Spawning in the same area for the entire team every time is a problem, although the temp invincibility is good, its not enough.



Ok so that is the things that i find an issue in the game that should need fixing.


THINGS I THINK THE GAME NEEDS.

-Bullet penetration please???? PLEASE!
- Make it harder somehow?, I avarage about 50-60 kills a game (1/3 of the kills needed to win). while the rest of my team is usually slacking, and I dont baserape either.
- Make ranks do something. Im level 7 right now and i havent gotten anything for it, the levels should do something.
-Change the damage of some guns? Please?
-Different gamemodes, TDM gets boring...
-I'm pretty sure if you get arround 10 kills you earn the same exp as someone with 50 kills, More kills should give you more EXP.
Ranking system, so you can see how good other players are,
-ingame KDR
-More maps?
-Objectives please?

So i would give this game a solid 9/10. Hope to see this game shine.
-Please Devs read this :D

reviewText: Early Access Review\n\nThe best way to describe this game is as nice mix of Counter-Strike and Call of Duty. The game has some issues with lag(at least on US servers), but the gun play is fun and fast paced. Much like in Counter-Strike, you save up money to buy weapons at the spawn. There are a decent amount of them so far, and I hope to see more added in the future. This game also isn't pay to win at all. The only real money you can spend is on cosmetics. Bottom line, give this game a chance. It may have a long way to go before it's complete, but it's still quite enjoyable as a timekiller if nothing else. The game is pretty small(under 300mb at the time of this review), so space shouldn't be an issue for most. Just download it and give it a try, you really have nothing to lose.

enjoy this if you're good at CS:GO and like some 'specials' you could also find in

need a little regeneration I will recommend this game with a 10/10.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

This game, is awesome !

It's familiar with games like CS:GO, COD, Battlefield, Crossfire.

PROS:
● It takes only 252MB Space, with no additional Updates / Patches.
● It's very enjoyable but also Skill-Based.
● It has a preffered time of play to an fixed amount of kills *150 kills*.
● It isn't a pay-to-win game, it only allowes you to buy customization items from the store.
● You can only get weapons in-game by killing the enemy team *300$ per kill* and you start with 2000$.
● It has good weapon prices in-game.
● The maps are medium sized. *Not very small but also not big*.
● It is very catchy, if you lose the game you are like  Oh
date:
let me play one more to avenge myself ".
● There are no hackers !!
● Enjoyful Graphics of old times mixed with modern graphics <3.

CONS● Only 5 maps.
● No drops in-game at end of match or while playing.
● Shotguns don't deal big damage and mid-range.
● AWP's are OP.
● You can easily get spawn-camped on some maps.
● It doesn't support GeForce ShadowPlay / Bandicam so far.
● Small Community.
● You can sometimes get spawned with free WH for 1 match / 1 death.
● Heavy Guns *Machine Guns* way too expensive.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thanks for reading

reviewText:
Early Access Review

This game is awesome.

WARMODE is a fast paced fps that is easy to learn. When you spawn, click B to buy items. You get money for kills and assists. Easy.

It's a very fair game. It's not pay to win, it's not team sided, and it's fun.

They coppied a lot from CS:GO, but it feels less stessful.

I don't know if there's a way to ban hackers, but for now you can kick them. I've only seen one so far.

If they made the graphics better, made it less laggy, and fixed the knife mechanic, it would be almost as good as CS:GO.

8/10 An awesome, fun, and stratigy filled game all in one for free.

The problem is as it is the game will not draw back players and this game that the developer(s) have made does however have potential to be a great multiplayer shooter but needs what I have put below would get 10/10 easy if these were changed.

Here are just a few things 6 things for the developers should consider to improve the game and also get loads of players playing their game.

1) Fix the frame rate issue runs just about smoothly but certain maps and games is abit hectic. The players hub looks dated just make it more interesting.

2) Targeting arrow and the shooting in the game needs tweaking abit so it is smoother sort of like call of duty games. Running around and shooting feels abit random and you shooting is abit  hit or miss when it comes to targeting the enemy and the yellow flash coming out of weapon thing is bad get rid of it and this would make this element of the game much better.

3) Better balance of weapons and when level up level should be able to buy improved parts for each weapon e.g sniper scope, laser scope, silencer, shock grenades, ammo carry limit parts, some modern weapons, or classic ones. Also armor and helmet upgrades and be able to change the colours of them.

Also attributes should be concidered and be capped to a ceratin level so is fair to other players e.g. speed, accuracy, agility, damage taken, amount of ammo you can carry, number of weapons you can carry would feel like the players are progressing.

4) Maps are interesting but could be more varied e.g water ones so you can go under water, swim mechnic, bushes, sand, street, urban areas.

n regarding places to hide and use for cover and for strategy is okay but their is no game play mechanics which you can use to your advantage and your group and of cource the enemy can use it also e.g cover mechanics behind walls, a low wall surface, box and also should be able to kneel behind it and use the zoom in target left mouse and aim and duck this would improve the overall stategy element without being to complicated. Also duck and crawl on floor for sneaky approachs and use the knife or to throw a grenade for a stealth ko would be a good idea.

5) Clear enemy detail on map marks where the enemy is e.g red for enemy, blue for friendly can be abit confusing since suits are all the same colour make it so one team is blue and the other red.

6) Should be able to smash windows, some enviroment damage, better detail in maps e.g cars, ruins, hotels, mansions, airport, dock some themed places.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Eh..with the game being in early access I pretty much expected bugs,etc. Don't get me wrong I do enjoy this game,but this game needs quite a bit of improvement.

First off,we need better servers or at least be able to see what the ping on the server is,i'm annoyed with entering in to a server and it lagging quite hard on me time to time and going back to smooth,etc.

What ever you do,DON'T aim down your sights! I experimented with it and when I was aiming at an enemy with my iron sights right on the person just to see all my bullets flying up in to the sky shooting the roof of the building. So you might as well just shoot from the hip.

If you get shot in the head with any gun pretty much,you'll fall over dead every time,so if you run across a hacker.aimbotter there is gonna be no way to exactly even be able to get enough time to even kill them,besides the fact this game has a spawn kill element in it,

Though on the bright side,at least it isn't P2W and you get a large variety of guns,but you just need to be able to get plenty enough kills to earn the money in order to have the guns you want,as my personal favourite is the ASVAL.

So despite the lag and spawn kill element,the game can be quite fun and possibly have potential in the near future..so I guess I can recomend it,I atleast had a lil bit of fun on the game.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Dustforce truly is a work of art. I don't mean that lightly. The way it's animated plus its music gives it that title in my book. I can find myself playing one level for an hour, maybe even hours at a time. The frustration of losing levels is filled with relaxation and calmness because of the ambient music. The way the levels are crafted is truly mindblowing. They had a system in which you had to perfect a level to earn a key, and you would use that key to earn more levels. In layman's terms, to earn more levels, you had to perfect current levels. They ditched that and added an XP system in which you gain more XP to earn a key the more levels you play and perfect. I'm very glad they added this system and was skeptical about buying it. But now that I did buy it, I do not regret it even for a second. One thing I really love about this game is how you don't have to unlock base levels. In a sense, this game is open world. That sense is that many levels are available to you, and you can choose whether you want to advance into more challenging levels, or stay where you're at. To get an S in completion, you have to sweep up EVERY leaf, and to get an S in Finesse, you have to maintain your combo throughout an entire level.

Another thing I absolutely enjoy about Dustforce is its expasive community. There are lots of Community Workshop maps for you to sharpen your skills on, and lots of people who can set a good example. I'm sure most of the people who get best times on all the levels have a Youtube channel, so you can probably catch them there. The community may or not be active, but it sure is good and friendly.

Overall, in terms of gameplay, music, artstyle, animation, and difficulty (it's not an easy game, but it's not that hard of a game either. It just depends on how much you want to play it), I rate this game:

10/10
BUY THIS GAME.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

For those of you who don't know, this was originally a mod for half life. It has sence been ported to steam on a new engine (Unity I think, but I may be wrong).

Is it a good gameThis is a small game with a Counter Strike / COD aproach. There are many bugs and it has bad lag, but overall I would say this game is fine. Don't rate it like it's suppost to be the next COD. For such a small game I find it very fun and relaxing to play. It is a good break form serious games like Counter Strike and other competitive FPS's.

Are there hackers?At the time of this review, there are no hackers. Everyone plays legit, and they even have a built in system so people (at the moment) can't speedhack, which would break the game. Once people start trying though, there will be hacks for this game. Once someone gets the address that calls the movement position, there will be speedhackers.

What would you rate this game?I would rate this game at about a 7/10. Sure it's not perfect, and has a fair share of bugs, but for such a small game I have to congratulate the developers. It is worth it to play this (quite fun) game.

For any developers reading this
There will be hackers in this game, but keep up the hard work :). Make sure that people can't just junk the call values to speedhack, otherwise there will be an abundance of speed hackers.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Eh..with the game being in early access I pretty much expected bugs,etc. Don't get me wrong I do enjoy this game,but this game needs quite a bit of improvement.

First off,we need better servers or at least be able to see what the ping on the server is,i'm annoyed with entering in to a server and it lagging quite hard on me time to time and going back to smooth,etc.

What ever you do,DON'T aim down your sights! I experimented with it and when I was aiming at an enemy with my iron sights right on the person just to see all my bullets flying up in to the sky shooting the roof of the building. So you might as well just shoot from the hip.

If you get shot in the head with any gun pretty much,you'll fall over dead every time,so if you run across a hacker.aimbotter there is gonna be no way to exactly even be able to get enough time to even kill them,besides the fact this game has a spawn kill element in it,

Though on the bright side,at least it isn't P2W and you get a large variety of guns,but you just need to be able to get plenty enough kills to earn the money in order to have the guns you want,as my personal favourite is the ASVAL.

So despite the lag and spawn kill element,the game can be quite fun and possibly have potential in the near future..so I guess I can recomend it,I atleast had a lil bit of fun on the game.

Dustforce truly is a work of art. I don't mean that lightly. The way it's animated plus its music gives it that title in my book. I can find myself playing one level for an hour, maybe even hours at a time. The frustration of losing levels is filled with relaxation and calmness because of the ambient music. The way the levels are crafted is truly mindblowing. They had a system in which you had to perfect a level to earn a key, and you would use that key to earn more levels. In layman's terms, to earn more levels, you had to perfect current levels. They ditched that and added an XP system in which you gain more XP to earn a key the more levels you play and perfect. I'm very glad they added this system and was skeptical about buying it. But now that I did buy it, I do not regret it even for a second. One thing I really love about this game is how you don't have to unlock base levels. In a sense, this game is open world. That sense is that many levels are available to you, and you can choose whether you want to advance into more challenging levels, or stay where you're at. To get an S in completion, you have to sweep up EVERY leaf, and to get an S in Finesse, you have to maintain your combo throughout an entire level.

Another thing I absolutely enjoy about Dustforce is its expasive community. There are lots of Community Workshop maps for you to sharpen your skills on, and lots of people who can set a good example. I'm sure most of the people who get best times on all the levels have a Youtube channel, so you can probably catch them there. The community may or not be active, but it sure is good and friendly.

Overall, in terms of gameplay, music, artstyle, animation, and difficulty (it's not an easy game, but it's not that hard of a game either. It just depends on how much you want to play it), I rate this game:

10/10
BUY THIS GAME.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Dustforce truly is a work of art. I don't mean that lightly. The way it's animated plus its music gives it that title in my book. I can find myself playing one level for an hour, maybe even hours at a time. The frustration of losing levels is filled with relaxation and calmness because of the ambient music. The way the levels are crafted is truly mindblowing. They had a system in which you had to perfect a level to earn a key, and you would use that key to earn more levels. In layman's terms, to earn more levels, you had to perfect current levels. They ditched that and added an XP system in which you gain more XP to earn a key the more levels you play and perfect. I'm very glad they added this system and was skeptical about buying it. But now that I did buy it, I do not regret it even for a second. One thing I really love about this game is how you don't have to unlock base levels. In a sense, this game is open world. That sense is that many levels are available to you, and you can choose whether you want to advance into more challenging levels, or stay where you're at. To get an S in completion, you have to sweep up EVERY leaf, and to get an S in Finesse, you have to maintain your combo throughout an entire level.

Another thing I absolutely enjoy about Dustforce is its expasive community. There are lots of Community Workshop maps for you to sharpen your skills on, and lots of people who can set a good example. I'm sure most of the people who get best times on all the levels have a Youtube channel, so you can probably catch them there. The community may or not be active, but it sure is good and friendly.

Overall, in terms of gameplay, music, artstyle, animation, and difficulty (it's not an easy game, but it's not that hard of a game either. It just depends on how much you want to play it), I rate this game:

10/10
BUY THIS GAME.

Things for the future:
More gamemodes

MOAR GUNS
Private matches
Anti-Cheat

I can't believe this was released in 2015. It's hilariously bad.
• 4/5 of the servers are Russian, the rest are US.
• Hit detection is 3/10.
• 90% of the time, melee attacks won't work. The hit detection on them is almost nonexistent. You can swing at the same person 20 times and never get a hit.
• Shooting anywhere other than the head is pointless. It takes way more shots and headshots are 1-3 shot kills depending on weapon and range. When not aiming for the head, it's actually possible to use an entire magazine and not get a kill.
• It always comes down to a spawn trap. Spawns in this game never change, so the good team just camps the opposing team's spawn until the game ends.
• You can easily stack teams, because you're allowed to switch mid-game.
• Grenade throwing and physics are bad, but manageable.
• Mid-game weapon buying works similarly to Counter Strike. Enter your spawn and press B to buy a new weapon, grenade or body armor. You can be shot at and die while doing this.
• Graphics, animations and just everything in general looks straight out of 2005. Minimal effort.
• VAC Secured, but that's not going to stop the inevitable flood of hackers from a bad free-to-play game. All it would take is a headshot aimbot and the game's dead.
• Some of the weapon sights are really bad. Famas, for example, fills half the screen while you look through a keyhole. Snipers don't even zoom in and their default zoom isn't much further than any other gun.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Warmode is a fast-paced first person shooter developed by WARTEAM.
Players choose between two sides in an ongoing conflict. Earn frags to accumulate points and upgrade your equipment, picking new guns from a large arsenal. Take down enemies up close with the shotgun, or hold back and pop headshots with an assortment of sniper rifles.
Fight across visually distinct and congested maps, where players are forced into tight corners—demanding a quick trigger-finger to survive. Each match is a team deathmatch where the first team to burn through the others’ lives wins.
Customize your avatar with an assortment of cosmetic items, such as masks and banners to distinguish yourself on the battlefield

reviewText:
Early Access Review

I have no idea why the dev released this game in this state. its broken. period. weapons are not balenced. serers are extreamly laggy. the only redeaming quality is the fact that even though this game features a store, you cant buy anything that puts pure free player at a disatvantage.
Was this game fun? yes it was. does that mean its a good game? no.

-=Gameplay=-
This game makes me think of counter-strike and COD had a baby and somehow that god aweful game Combat Arms also came in. It plays alot like Counter-Strike, you only get weapons by killing other players and getting points. But the problem lies in the fact that the servers are so laggy you cant ever get a kill. not to mention aiming seems to be slightly off when you use your aim down sights. there is only 1 U.S server and for the most part my connection to each server remained crap. Now dont get me wrong, i did enjoy some of the matches. but its hard to denie this game has alot of flaws that quite honestly are un-exseptable. The maps feel bland. you can see obvious choke points and sections where most players are going to be. but these highly populated areas are the only place there tends to be any action. Spawn camping is another big problem. if the enemy team has more players you can bet your gonna get spawn camped.

-=Sound=-
The game tends to be glitchy at times. the guns also dont sound all that amazing. the music you here when you start up the game is nice. but after that is all guns. and thats fine...if the guns were nice to hear.

-=Community=-
With this being a pure online based game i have to adress community. the community is....there. but its not booming. i havent seen too much hacker" name calling while in a game as of late. but when thegame was first released
date:
it was somthing you saw alot.

-=Free or Pay2Win=-
This game does feature a store so the dev can get alittle cash dollar. but theres no guns
hoursPlayed:
or anything that would make it pay 2 win. what is there is slight cosmetic gear. such as face pain and masks.

-=Graphics=-
The graphics are not anything new
voteText: exciteing
helpfulPercent:
or all that special. but they are not the worst. i can deal with the graphics if the gameplay is good.

-=Final verdict=-
This game is fun

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Very odd game. Despite everyone's review after playing about 12 minutes of the game..thats all you pretty much need to make an opinion of this game. Graphics are good for 250MBs and gameplay really feels like Call of Duty. One thing that surprised me was how accurate the hit detection is, however the illogical lag makes you struggle to get a kill. Also, about the hit detection, it seems that they made the head hitbox about 70% of the player model, any kill you get almost always gets you a headshot. Weapons feel and look good however some weapons definitly need to be nerfed or require a bigger point requirement. Spawns are also a problem, you can pretty much tell where they will spawn and there is no spawn protection at all so you can probably get about 150 kills in just about 20 minutes. In the end, this is a shooter that has a lot of potential and definitly requires attention.

6/10

Pros:
-Accurate hit detection
-Looks decent for 250MBs

Cons:
-Spawns need work
-No spawn protection
-Over powered weapons
-Server lag

Early Access Review

This game is a First Person Shooter if you havent noticed already. I have to say that this game is a rip-off of CS:GO but lacks the depth like planting bombs and such. I only played this game because a Steam friend of mine parted with his sanity and played this game so much that he changed his Steam name to 'WARMODE KING'. I wrote this review to save you from such dark actions.

Because this is a PC game Graphics are everything, but this game does not deliver in this respect. It resembles a potato on methamphetamine quite well. The objects and environment are of low quality and the textures are sub-par. The animations aren't horrible but they take to long to complete, for example i might go to shoot an enemy but they are already dead and i cant see this because the death animation takes to long to finish.
The maps are terrible and arent very detailed, with few static environmental objects. They also lack complecity and are far off something such as CS:GO.
To be honest i cant be bothered writing a review for this game its not worth the pain and regretful gameplay. Just save your life from a slow death from this game and just buy CS:GO.

This is a cheap, little, fun shooter. It Is truly free to play, only things in the shop are Payday style masks. Graphics are kinda dated, but if less lighting effents get me 120 fps, i think is a good trade.
Guns are the usual deal, Ak-47 , SMGs, M4a4, snipers etc. There are some balance issues, shotguns deal almost no dmg, and most smg insta-kill on headshot. Weirdly, most guns have almost no recoil when using iron sights"
date: but a lot when using "hip fire"\nThe game has an in-match shop like Counter-strike
recommended: but you keep your weapons and armor between lives (you buy armor once
hoursPlayed: you spawn with armor everytime).\nThe only game-mode i saw was Team-Deathmatch
voteText: but the devs say they will add more.\nMaybe not the best free shooter out there

Lets just start by saying this game sucks.
The menu has nothing nice about it; it's a complete eyesore.
The graphics look like they were done in 2006 and there is no antialiasing even when aa is turned on.
The guns take too long to actually deal a decent ammount of damage to players. They also feel crappy to shoot due to the lack of characteristic and the ammount of input lag thrown into the mix.
The buy menu is horrid to look at and use.
Ecosystem in team deathmatch?

reviewText:
Early Access Review

People who downvoted this game, ITS IN EARLY ACESS. That means things will change, they will implement things better, add new things, make it fun, ya know? I put only 3.6 hours into it and i already find it quite fun. Let me break down the game a bit and what I think are the pros and cons of this game so far:

PROS:
Great graphics for an early acess! They are amazing for a free to play shooter!
Gameplay is fast-paced, very fun.
The gun selection is quite nice, although some, like the AK47 and the AUG need a bit of balancing.
CONS:
The teams can get out of balance incredibly quick. it could be a 3v1 and I have seen games as far away as 5v2. Although I have seen some good players, they aren't that good.
The semiauto shotgun is a bit op, as it does a lot of damage from a farther range you are used to.
There is only one game mode at the moment. Even though it is still an amazing game for early access, one game mode puts me off a bit.
Most of the weapons you can get a tapshoot kill with, which is dissapointing, because i would rather have only a few weapons that that can one hit kill, which would mean balancing out all of the assault rifles, and balancing up the smgs.

All in all, a great game for early acess. Recommend it for experienced gamers. Great job WARTEAM!

reviewText: Early Access Review\n\nThe movement is buggy, crouching is buggy, the mouse movement is laggy and feels non-responsive. The servers suck, the UI is trash and the community is whining about hackers all the time (most of it is just lag from my experience). The guns are ridiculously op, the spawns are broken, there are angles that provide immense advantage (others players can't shoot you), there is no need for iron sights. However, I had loads of fun playing this game. Headshotting from 2km away with a pistol is satisfying. The game is really small in size and for the time being it is truly f2p. I like the point system to buy guns but I think you should be able to gain points over time. Also more options should be implemented (FOV slider for example). The game needs a lot of work but it has the potential to have something going for it as far as I am concerned. Overall, I thought the game was fun and I could oversee the flaws. I recommend it if you want to pass some free time. In the future I might revisit it and maybe change my recommendation but for the time being this game is fairly fun.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

Well the idea of this game is great. It has unique features and has good graphics for a free game. In fact, I would say that this is a pretty awesome FPS game and I usually hate FPS games. But notice how I said WOULD... Thats because although the game is there, the most important things for an FPS game to have aren't! What I mean by that is half of the time your bullets damage an enemy and half of the time they don't. Also the assist system is so ♥♥♥♥ing bad that I cant even comprehend it. But my favorite flaw, other than all of the maps being as big as my bathroom, is the random suicide deaths. I'll just be standing there and out of nowhere I die and it says I was killed by me. Now I cant for the life of me figure out what is causing this, it's just completely random.
I really hope that this game is in its beta because it is so close to being a great game. All the game makers need to do is add a North American Channel for servers and fix the major bugs involoved with causing damage, the assist system, add larger maps, and fix the kill system. I would recommend that you try the game for 30 minutes tops and then delete it. I feel that you will agree with me that this game has potential, it just needs some major fixes.

reviewText:
Early Access Review

People who downvoted this game, ITS IN EARLY ACESS. That means things will change, they will implement things better, add new things, make it fun, ya know? I put only 3.6 hours into it and i already find it quite fun. Let me break down the game a bit and what I think are the pros and cons of this game so far:

PROS:
Great graphics for an early acess! They are amazing for a free to play shooter!
Gameplay is fast-paced, very fun.
The gun selection is quite nice, although some, like the AK47 and the AUG need a bit of balancing.
CONS:
The teams can get out of balance incredibly quick. it could be a 3v1 and I have seen games as far away as 5v2. Although I have seen some good players, they aren't that good.
The semiauto shotgun is a bit op, as it does a lot of damage from a farther range you are used to.
There is only one game mode at the moment. Even though it is still an amazing game for early access, one game mode puts me off a bit.
Most of the weapons you can get a tapshoot kill with, which is dissapointing, because i would rather have only a few weapons that that can one hit kill, which would mean balancing out all of the assault rifles, and balancing up the smgs.

All in all, a great game for early acess. Recommend it for experienced gamers. Great job WARTEAM!

What a crap. Dont believe the reviews who compare this to CS:GO or COD. This is maybe graphically a maybe bit enhanced compared to CS 1.6 but in all other terms WORSE than CS 1.6 (yes, I m talking about CS 1.6, not GO, not Source... the OLD one).

Playing this is like watching a stop motion picture with very bad and always funny behaviour of the models. Weapon handling is so crappy CS:GO is like driving a mercedes compared to this.

Plus, maps are boring, repetetive, uninspired. I rather play CS 1.6 with deathmatch mode, 10x more fun...

reviewText:
Early Access Review

People who downvoted this game, ITS IN EARLY ACESS. That means things will change, they will implement things better, add new things, make it fun, ya know? I put only 3.6 hours into it and i already find it quite fun. Let me break down the game a bit and what I think are the pros and cons of this game so far:

PROS:
Great graphics for an early acess! They are amazing for a free to play shooter!
Gameplay is fast-paced, very fun.
The gun selection is quite nice, although some, like the AK47 and the AUG need a bit of balancing.
CONS:
The teams can get out of balance incredibly quick. it could be a 3v1 and I have seen games as far away as 5v2. Although I have seen some good players, they aren't that good.
The semiauto shotgun is a bit op, as it does a lot of damage from a farther range you are used to.
There is only one game mode at the moment. Even though it is still an amazing game for early access, one game mode puts me off a bit.
Most of the weapons you can get a tapshoot kill with, which is dissapointing, because i would rather have only a few weapons that that can one hit kill, which would mean balancing out all of the assault rifles, and balancing up the smgs.

All in all, a great game for early acess. Recommend it for experienced gamers. Great job WARTEAM!
